Most frequently used commands:

ui <domain> <server>	                        displays domain/account information
dig <domain>
inodes <server> <path>	                      shows a breakdown of inodes based on a path
loggrep [search keyword] <httpd|messages|exim|cpanelerror|cpanelaccess|cpanelaccounting|ssh|dovecot|mysql|ftp> <server>	        search from various logs on our servers
logtail <server|ip|domain> <httpd|messages|exim|cpanelerror|cpanelaccess|cpanelaccounting|ssh|dovecot|mysql|ftp> [search keyword]	tails various error logs. ctrl-c to quit
scan
scanlog
dcbackuplist
checkautossl





clear	                                        clears your screen
history	                                        displays your recent GatorShell history
ui <domain> <server>	                        displays domain/account information
dig <domain>
countproc <domain> <server>	                checks current number of processes for a user
du <domain>	                                displays disk usage and inode usage on a server
inodes <server> <path>	                        shows a breakdown of inodes based on a path
quota <domain> <server>	                        check current quota for a user (includes inodes)
status <service> <server>	                returns the status of a service running on a server

createinfo <domain> <server>	                create a phpinfo page  in the users public_html dir

loggrep [search keyword] <httpd|messages|exim|cpanelerror|cpanelaccess|cpanelaccounting|ssh|dovecot|mysql|ftp> <server>	        search from various logs on our servers
logtail <server|ip|domain> <httpd|messages|exim|cpanelerror|cpanelaccess|cpanelaccounting|ssh|dovecot|mysql|ftp> [search keyword]	tails various error logs. ctrl-c to quit

secinfo <domain> <server>	                        check a domain for mod_security blocks
whitelist <domain> <action> <server> <ruleids>  	whitelist a domain for certain mod_security rules


dropjail <domain> <server> [port]	        drops into a client’s jailshell (SSH into the customer's account) - server is required when port is specified
killproc <domain> <server>	                kills all current processes for a user
permfix <domain> <server>	                resets permissions on public_html and all subfiles/folders for a user
pwtemp <action> <target> <server> [-d]	        set/remove temp password for a user or e-mail address (Plesk sup- port added: setplesk). -d will permanently reset the password for setuser, setmail, and setwp


checkzone <domain> <server>	                tests if there is any errors in a domain’s zonefile
host <hostname> or <ip>	                        host lookup for IP or hostname
ping <domain> <numpings>	                pings a domain until ctrl-c’d or until numpings is reached
rblcheck <ip>	                                checks an IP against RBLs
viewzone <domain>	                        views a DNS zone file from the server
checkblacklist <ip>	                        check if an ip is on the exim blacklist
checkfire

rldomcheck <domain> <server>	                checks whether domain is in localdomains or remotedomains
scan
scanlog
eximparser
resusage
forcessl
hamlookup
cplogtable
dupath
killdns


Backup:
dcbackuplist
dcbackuprestore
scanbackup

resetcpanel
iskilled
vdetect
checkautossl


